# Project Structure Guide

This is a personal blog website project with a modern, responsive design. The main components are:

## Core Files
- [index.html](mdc:index.html): The main entry point that defines the website structure and content
- [styles.css](mdc:styles.css): Contains all styling rules including responsive design and layout

## Assets
- `icons/`: Contains social media icons (e.g., Instagram)
- `images/`: Stores website images including profile photos

## Key Features
1. Responsive Design
   - Desktop: Split layout with sidebar (20%) and main content (80%)
   - Mobile: Stacked layout with hamburger menu
   - Tablet: Adaptive layout with optimized spacing

2. Typography
   - Primary font: 'Play' by Jonas Hecksher
   - Font Awesome icons for social links
   - Responsive text sizing

3. Components
   - Navigation sidebar with logo
   - Social media links
   - Mobile-friendly menu
   - Image display area
   - Bio text section
